gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 118, Jazz 110
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors move to 43-35 on the year as they defeated the Jazz, 118-110. Klay Thompson led Golden State with 32 points, five rebounds, and four assists while Jonathan Kuminga added 21 points, 10 rebounds, and four assists in his return from a six-game absence. Brandin Podziemski totaled 16 points, seven rebounds, and six assists in the win. Johnny Juzang had a career-high 27 points for Utah in the loss. The Jazz fall to 29-49.
